# üìù Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## Product Name: NoteLink Pro  
**Type:** Cross-platform Note-Taking + Enterprise Sales Enablement App  
**Owner:** Enolda Joseph  
**Last Updated:** July 15, 2025  

---

## 1. Overview

**Goal:**  
Develop a high-performance, secure note-taking application tailored for enterprise sales teams. The app must integrate with existing tools like Evernote and OneNote, with advanced features such as CRM sync, sales playbooks, AI summaries, voice-to-text, and secure note sharing for team collaboration and client interactions.

**Target Users:**  
- Enterprise Account Executives  
- Sales Enablement Teams  
- Client Success Managers  
- BDRs/SDRs  
- Field Reps  

---

## 2. Key Features & Requirements

### üîÑ Cross-Platform Bridging
- Evernote & OneNote Importer (preserve folders, tags, formatting)
- Two-Way Sync API Integration with Evernote and OneNote
- Chrome Extension for web clipping

### üìä Enterprise Sales Optimization
- CRM Integrations (Salesforce, HubSpot, Zoho)
- Attach Notes to Deals, Contacts, or Accounts
- Sales Playbooks and Battlecards Repository
- Discovery/Demo/QBR Note Templates
- Follow-up Email Generator (powered by AI)

### üß† AI-Powered Productivity
- AI Summarization (TL;DR)
- Voice-to-Text Transcription (real-time)
- Automatic Tagging based on context

### üîê Security & Compliance
- Role-based Permissions (Private, Team, Org)
- End-to-End Encryption
- Audit Logs for Access & Edits

### üåê Collaboration Tools
- Team Workspaces by Region, Team, or Account
- Real-Time Co-Editing
- Client-Friendly Export View (sanitized)

### üì± Platform Support
- Web (React-based SPA)
- iOS and Android mobile apps
- Desktop app via Electron

---

## 3. User Stories (Epics & Examples)

### Epic 1: Note Creation & Capture
- As a rep, I want to create meeting notes using voice-to-text so I can focus on my client.
- As a user, I want to import notes from Evernote and OneNote to avoid duplicate work.

### Epic 2: CRM + Sales Enablement Integration
- As a rep, I want to link notes to Salesforce deals so I can track engagement context.
- As a manager, I want to view and coach from my team‚Äôs sales notes.

### Epic 3: Collaboration & Sharing
- As a rep, I want to co-edit live notes with my team during a call.
- As a rep, I want to share sanitized notes externally with clients.

### Epic 4: AI-Driven Workflows
- As a user, I want a quick summary of my long meeting notes.
- As a user, I want AI to suggest follow-up tasks based on content.

### Epic 5: Data Governance
- As an admin, I want to set permissions for editing and viewing.
- As an IT manager, I want audit logs for compliance.

---

## 4. Success Metrics

- 85%+ of enterprise users connect at least one external note source  
- 90%+ accuracy in voice-to-text transcription  
- 3+ minutes average time saved per note via AI summary  
- 20%+ increase in CRM note logging compliance  
- <5s average load time across all platforms  

---

## 5. Risks & Mitigation

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| API rate limits from Evernote/OneNote | Background queueing + token refresh system |
| Complexity of CRM integrations | Start with Salesforce MVP, stagger rollouts |
| Privacy concerns for note content | End-to-end encryption + user-controlled permissions |

